    {
      "id": "92214eb523e9cab108dd6cd8d036d652cf48a3db",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-21 18:35:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nAdding the (diff > OBD_MAX_PRECREATE) check complicates this patch unnecessarily, and will likely break some use cases. In particular, if an OST is restored from backup, or for some reason LAST_ID is lost and recreated to match the highest objid but is considerably lower than the MDS lov_objids value, then this OST can no longer be used by the MDS.\n\nThere is an old patch by Lai about handling these cases properly at mount time (reconstructing LAST_ID, and skipping object precreation if too many objects are requested after some recovery).\n\nIn any case, we shouldn't be adding this complexity into this patch (which should just be for reducing the precreate count for small OSTs).\n\nSorry I didn't catch this on the previous inspection.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "b613c4deecf2ca7e18d239fe12ae50c292b71f72",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-21 18:40:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nhmm, correct...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
