      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "d95cf2ae7c47a7cdbb124730b625756f311a8977",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 05:16:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nIs this going to negatively affect performance on such small systems too? Should we be worried about it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "5dc8a78beb2e13f5cbecaf50d18eb36dd20dfc7f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 05:28:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nw/o this patch osd will be complaining about too large transactions a lot and this can affect performance.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "5c6681573847cc0a5a34ea6693b0bf92008dc1a9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 08:15:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nOleg, it can't be any worse than before there were batched creations (i.e. any 1.x or 2.[123] releases. In any case, thus problem us mostly only affecting testing systems with smaller-than-default journal size.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "198ec345c0d3f5194c8d6e651e599b9e17a06d89",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 18:14:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nWell, I am running one of those smaller systems and so trying to assess what the impact might be.\n\nWe did have batched precreates before, did not we? Default was to create at least 32 objects per precreate request.\n\nOr is this something else?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "d89a1b044cc6b52e904273e7e064c209da2196e0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 18:16:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nthe purpose of this batching is to create few objects within a single local transaction (reported to be helpful for LLNL). obdfilter creates a new transaction for every object being created. this is why Andreas said it can be any worse than obdfilter.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "091015074d758932f601aeaee8115b646bd05b05",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 18:17:26.000000000",
      "message": "Change has been successfully cherry-picked as 71eb67f041732093696781cc3ddddb7d9aac66a6.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    }
